<br />I have the first one, for some 15 years already, and it works just as well as the first time I ever used it. And it did fall and hit the floor a few times in the past, when I was a sloppy kid. I just had to buy some new controllers eventually. It has A/V out (using a special connector, not hard to find or build) and the stereo output with volume control on the front (something some of the later models lacked). Never hooked it to a Sega CD, 32X or Master system adapter, so I can't say how well it works with those.

		

